21/10/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Prime Minister Adrian Nastase announced Monday (20 October) that he accepted the resignations of the ministers of European Integration Hildegard Puwak, Health Minister Mircea Beuran and Minister for Government Co-ordination Serban Mihailescu.
Nastase also announced replacements -- Vasile Puscas, Ionel Blanculescu and Eugen Bejenariu, respectively.
The three ministers stepped down amid strong public pressure after their names surfaced in separate scandals.
(ACT Media - 21/10/03;
Rompres - 20/10/03)
